    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Business Implications of Incoterms With Respect To Export Performance – Special Reference to Paper Industry</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Jeyavel N</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Business Implications<br />Export Performance</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5869</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Some companies think that the INCOTERMS rules show where title/ownership passes. They do not. INCOTERMS rules only relate to the physical movement of good and indicate how costs should be divided and where risk passes. The passing of risk has nothing to do with title.
Because the right and obligations of the sellers and buyers bear certain similarities across different Incoterms, parties may easily get confused. However, if the underlying principles of INCOTERMS are fully understood, then it should not be too difficult to differentiate of INCOTERM from the another.
In sum, the INCOTERMS are a very useful mechanism for smoothing the path of international sales transactions. This is only true, however, if both seller and buyer take time to acquaint themselves with the INCOTERMS and their responsibilities under specific terms. Only then can reasoned decisions be made about the correct INCOTERM to use in a given situation.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/11168">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/11168</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
